@node "Welcome" "Welcome to Amiga Information Online"
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
                          Editorial By Chris Seward
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
  Welcome, we're in p-a-r-t-y atmosfere here, as we have now been officially
running for 1 whole year, its been hard to get through and it's been alot
of hard work and effort but I think it's been worth it. We've got a jam
packed issue this time, with thousands or reviews, articles and everything.

  Still no news on anything really Amiga related, no hints at when we can
expect the new workbench or the new amiga, so we'll all sit back and take
it easy until they reviel the monster amiga that's to come!

  Wooow, one whole year in production, seems like a long time but it has
actually flown by and doesn't even seem that long ago since i first started
up AIO. The issues now are much better than the first issue and it looks
alot better to, with music and a picture at the start of the issue it is
more friendly looking. The actual guide is also more pleasent to read and
the layout it easier to use compared to the first couple of issues.

 I suppose your wondering why this issue is around 3 weeks late eh? Well
the main reason is because it is the biggest issue ever and it took ages
to put together. Another reasons was that this month must have been the
dryest month for utils/games and any news or articles to do so I had to
search far and hard to bring you the features and reviews in the issue.
Oh well never mind maybe there'll be more exciting news next month!

 A bit of of a sad state of affairs is Psygnosis, I was in contact with
them just before Christmas '97 asking them if it was possible to interview
them for AIO regarding the Amiga and would they consider comming back
to it now the PPC and various well known games have been released for it
etc. The person I was in contact with agreed to the interview but now
after 4 months of continues emails to him he fails to reply, if you would
like to pester him about an interview for AIO then email him at :
@{b}Paul.Hanley@psygnosis.co.uk@{ub}  -  and ask why he will not give an interview
for AIO, please pester him about this if you can as I would really like
to know and alot of readers would probably like to know the answers to
some of those questions, mention how he can get in contact with me via
email.

 A good article to check out this month is the work-in-progress about
the game Domination by the Amiga1 team, it gives you in full details the
problems they have had to overcome and where they are upto with the
game, i'll look forwards to receiving the next parts.

 Well thats all I have to say for this month, next issue will be released
a bit later than the usual 'saturday nearest to the 20th' date because this
issue was released so late but it will get back on track very soon. Hope
you liked this issue and I will look fowards to you reading next issue!
 
 If @{B}Pom Lekey@{ub} sysop of Jipebo BBS in Sweden is reading please get in touch
with the editor at : @{B}Cool@DCandy.demon.co.uk@{ub} as he has lost your
email address!

