@node "gr2" "Air Fight"

@{fg shine} Air Fight@{fg text}

 This is a simple shoot-the-plane game for one or two players. The author 
recommends 2-players because algorithm for computer plane is very simple, 
so is relative easy to shoot him down. (Well, thats what the author said)

 The game is based on `Super Dogfight' which first appeared on the C64. It 
has a host load of options, including collision detection and amount 
of hit points each plane has.

 Another option is what background and screen res you want, the standard 
background is easiest to play on, the other two, cheese, and clouds are 
really difficult as there are only a few places that you can actually see 
your plane, because either the cheese of cloud are blocking your view. The 
screen res is an intresting option, when you press FIRE to play you have to
wait for a while, you are not told why, there is no disk activity so I 
don`t know whats going on, anyway, the more pixels you have on your screen 
the longer you have to wait, and the planes are smaller, giving you more 
space to fly, but i`d stick with the low res if I was you.

 The game itself is rather playable, the idea is to shoot down the other 
plane, you do this by pressing fire and hope it hits. The computer player 
is not that good, it just spins around and fires every now and again. The 
authors right to recommend 2 players! The only trouble I had, is when a 
plane gets hit, the game pauses for a bit, and if the other plane keeps 
firing there is no where to go and you`ll die really quickly!

 Overall this is a simple game, the sounds are simple, the gameplay easy, 
but, to be honest it won`t last you that long.

