 ProGammon is a Back Gammon game for 1 player, who plays against the 
intellegent computer, the author claims that his ProGammon has the most 
intellegent computer player, and he has thought of everything, he has even 
tested the random dice rolls just to check the computer can`t cheat, and 
hes but the C source in the Amiga Guide documentation!

 The game opens its own screen, and personally I think the palette colours 
are horrible (Look at the screenshot), but thank the heavens, you can 
change the colours by clicking on Palette in the pull-down menus!

 The instructions in the Amiga Guide, and not that clear for the beginner, 
like me, i`ve never played Back Gammon and I didn`t have a clue how to 
play it, so when I atempted to have a game, I did not get anywhere!

 A nice feature in this game is that it keeps a log of all your scores, so 
you can see how many times you beat or lose against the computer, the 
author claims there is a 50/50 possibility of winning, even Stevens' then.

 I can`t really say that much about this game, it is surposed to play a 
good game of Back Gammon with you, but as I can`t play it, I can`t tell 
you if this is true, because I can`t play it!

 This game is not for the beginner, if you are an expert Back Gammon 
player get this and see if you can beat the computer!

