@node "gr5" "Shootist"

@{fg shine} Shootist@{fg text}

 In Shootist you must shoot at these people wo are in different buildings, 
the characters are nothing special, but the gameplay is very good.

 Each level is split into two stages, in the first stages you have to shoot
the men in the buildings, the first level, for example, is set in the Wild 
West, and you have to shoot the bad guys while avoiding the sherifs who 
wear badges. The second stage on the first level involves you shooting 
butterflies of different colours, if your pointer goes on top of a 
butterfly which isn`t the right colour you loose strength.

 This all sounds simple, but you get 30 ammo units, and the ammo re-filles 
don`t fall down that often. You also get so much strength, and if the men 
shoot at you so many times your dead!

 You also get to decide your skill level, SLOW, is easy, and the shareware 
demo is completed in no time, NORMAL is fairly challenging, but again is 
easy, the hardest is the HARD level, the men move very fast, and you can 
rarly hit them!

 The only thing I don`t particually like about this one is the dark colours
in the palette, they look horrible, but give the game more of an eary look.

 This is a shareware demo, the author would like US$5.00 for the full 
version, I think that is too much, you only get the first level in the 
demo, and in the docs it says there are only four levels anyway! The full 
game should be FREEWARE!

