@node "gr7" "Boum"

@{fg shine} Boum@{fg text}

 Boum is your standard MineSweeper clone. The object is to find out the 
locations of all the mines in the mine field, when you click somewhere you 
are either killed by a mine, you uncover some uneffected ground, or you get
a number telling you how many mines are around that spot, its all chance 
from here!

 There is not special about this game, you can select between three skill 
levels, and 3 grid sizes (The one in the screenshot is `Big').

 What I really like about this game is the sounds, the explosion is cool, 
the others are rather simple, but it really inhanses the gameplay.

 Overall, this is a fairly average effot, I have seen better, but this is 
worth the time downloading just to mess about on every now and again when 
you are bored!

