@node "gr8" "Football Simulation"

@{fg shine} The Footy Game@{fg text}

 The Footy Game is a football simulator, it loads on your Workbench screen 
and you select the names of two teams, and then you select three strickers.
You can also click on the TEAM A or TEAM B buttons and scroll through the 
database of Premier League teams!

 When you click on play to get the main screen. Now, in a Footy Game you 
would expect a few players, a goal, and a ball, you get none of this in 
this game, it is texted based!

 Each game lasts 90 seconds and time is held at half time which occurs 
after 45 seconds. Every now and again some writing will appear informing 
you what is going on, you either get shots at goal, or you get players 
injured! Not much help.

 Something nice about the game is the front-end. The windows look nice, and
are well presented. Its just a shame the game isn`t the same.

 In the end this game is not that good, there are no graphics, and the best
bit in the game is the clock hand which rotates! There is no point to this 
game, the only use I can think of, is to amuse you while you are waiting 
for a disk to copy of something!

