@node "gr10" "Bloog"

@{fg shine} Bloog@{fg text}

 Bloog was out doing his morning walk, when he all of a sudden 
caught sight of a tower, almost touching the clouds with its peek. He 
walked towards the building and noticed a sign, saying: "This is a deserted
Maze.  Do  NOT  enter!" Bloog, whose brain wasn't more evolved than a PC,
wrecked the sign and opened the tower's door. He stepped in, and the door
slammed behind him. He was locked inside.

 You monitor Bloog and has got to help him through a load of maze-floors  
to  get  to  the top - from where Bloog can easily jump down to the ground 
outside. That Bloog is a green blob with big eyes and equaly large feet, 
a mouth and no arms.

 Bloog comes from the same group of people as C.A.N.E, the idea behind this
one is to find a set of keys. Sometimes, keys can be on the floor when  
you enter a level. Most keys though, are hidden inside colored blocks. If 
you smack two blocks together, and if they are the same colour, both 
blocks will disappear and a key will pop up. But if the blocks are  
different colours, the one being hit will be destroyed while the otherone 
remains intact. Blocks can also be painted with another colour!

 This is only a demo, but the full version is FREE! The author doesn`t 
think it is that good, but this is brilliant! The limitations are as 
follows:

 · No intro and end-of-game animations.
 · You can't save the hiscores.
 · The game doesn't accept more than 10 levels
 · Only one piece of ingame-music

 These limitations don`t really make any difference to the gameplay, it is 
simply brilliant, some of the puzzles take ages to work out, and with all 
the special objects you can collect and use to your advantage, this game 
will keep you on the edge of your seat, at least until you finish the 8th 
level, (the last one). But then, there is more, there is a Bloog level 
editor which allows you and your mates to make even more levels!!!!!

 If you haven`t guessed already, I really like this game, I think you will 
too, just download the demo, and the full version is free, what are you 
waiting for?? Well, read the rest of the mag first!

