@node "ur2" "FiDED V39.547"

@{fg shine} FiDED V39.547@{fg text}

 Alot of files today come with File_ID.DIZs when they are packed so it is
easier for you to find out what the program is without having to actually
read the docs or run the program. They are also used on nearly every
bullitain board going. It allows you to pack a short description of the
file into the archive so once you've uploaded it the BBS automatically
can read this file and saves you having to type in what the file is and
what it does.

 It can be a pain when you download files and the archive, text or whatever
name gives you no indication to what the file actually is so you have to 
spend time dearchiving your files to see exactly what they are. This is
where FiDED comes in handy, you select your directory, with the files in
and it will grab all the descriptions of the files that enclude File_ID.Dizs
and place them in an easy to read text file. The text file gives you the
name of the archive, the size of it and what the file_id.diz says. The 
archives or texts that don't have a file_id.diz it will skip and tell
you in the text file that there is no description for that file.

 Overall File-Id Extractor Deluxe is a must for anyone who wants to
easily find out what the files are. Make sure you get hold of this, it'll
save you plenty of time in the future.

